HEADWORD: Thoracica
<hw>Tho*rac"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of cirripeds
including those which have six thoracic segments, usually bearing six
pairs of cirri. The common barnacles are examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

